ary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering testing strategies**\\n\\nI'm thinking that maybe using public fields and getField could be a better approach to avoid complications with getDeclaredField in the test. I wonder if the public API example in the documentation utilizes getDeclaredField. Using getDeclaredField directly in the test might be necessary to cover the call site effectively. It's really about finding the right balance for testing against various accesses!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering Java access modifiers**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the top-level test cases, noting the public and nested public static final elements. It seems like I could assert fieldSource.getName or declaring class rather than just checking for equality. The field equals check might be for a field object with the same name, class, or type, so that’s fine. I need to address whether the user is asking for an \\\"active dynamic-access class\\\" and keep it organized within its own Java file. Currently, there isn’t one available. I should write it!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_H73iOEzNVrUIKb9zqhuZOYsD|fc_02a9f9400f418b850169f5b24f08ac819297512baf3c69f99c", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework/spring-core/5.3.15/src/test/java/org_springframework/spring_core/SerializableTypeWrapperInnerFieldTypeProviderTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_springframework.spring_core;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.ByteArrayInputStream;\nimport java.io.ByteArrayOutputStream;\nimport java.io.IOException;\nimport java.io.ObjectInputStream;\nimport java.io.ObjectOutputStream;\nimport java.lang.reflect.Field;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.springframework.core.ResolvableType;\n\npublic class SerializableTypeWrapperInnerFieldTypeProviderTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void restoresFieldProviderDuringDeserialization() throws Exception {\n        Field field = SampleType.class.getField(\"value\");\n        ResolvableType resolvableType = ResolvableType.forField(field);\n\n        ResolvableType restoredType = serializeAndDeserialize(resolvableType);\n\n        assertThat(restoredType.resolve()).isEqualTo(String.class);\n        assertThat(restoredType.getSource()).isInstanceOf(Field.class);\n        Field restoredField = (Field) restoredType.getSource();\n        assertThat(restoredField).isEqualTo(field);\n        assertThat(restoredField.getDeclaringClass()).isEqualTo(SampleType.class);\n        assertThat(restoredField.getName()).isEqualTo(\"value\");\n    }\n\n    private static ResolvableType serializeAndDeserialize(ResolvableType resolvableType)\n            throws IOException, ClassNotFoundException {\n        ByteArrayOutputStream output = new ByteArrayOutputStream();\n        try (ObjectOutputStream objectOutput = new ObjectOutputStream(output)) {\n            objectOutput.writeObject(resolvableType);\n        }\n        try (ObjectInputStream objectInput = new ObjectInputStream(new ByteArrayInputStream(output.toByteArray()))) {\n            return (ResolvableType) objectInput.readObject();\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class SampleType {\n\n        public String value;\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1215, "output": 1297, "cacheRead": 18432, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 20944, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777709633353, "responseId": "resp_02a9f9400f418b850169f5b241c2dc8192b487b330b9cde2ff"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_H73iOEzNVrUIKb9zqhuZOYsD|fc_02a9f9400f418b850169f5b24f08ac819297512baf3c69f99c", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"ty